{"word":"H579 - אָנָה - ʼânâh - aw-naw' - Befall","slug":"H579","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אָנָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼânâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-naw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Befall"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05E0;&#x05D4; - 'a&#x0302;na&#x0302;h</b> - <i>aw-naw'</i><p/>A primitive root (perhaps rather identical with <a href=\"#/H578\">H578</a> through the idea of <i>contraction</i> in anguish); to <i>approach</i>; hence to <i>meet</i> in various senses: - befall, deliver, happen, seek a quarrel."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8385\">H8385</a>"}]}